FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782362901
OL,3,CForecasters warn of even higher
OL,4,Ctemperatures amid sweltering heatwave
OL,6,FThe heatwave forecast is set to
OL,7,Fcontinue on Thursday and Friday, and
OL,8,Fthe Met Office said it is possible the
OL,9,Ffigure could be "beaten again".
OL,11,FWednesday's high breaks the previous
OL,12,Ftop temperature for June of 35.6C in
OL,13,F1976 and 1957, the forecaster said.
OL,15,FThe Met Office said that the
OL,16,Fexceptional heat will spread
OL,17,Fnorthwards on Thursday, "with an even
OL,18,Fhotter day ahead for some with amber
OL,19,Fand red extreme heat warnings in
OL,20,Fforce".
OL,26,@qD@QOUqD@^O]yD@YOU|D@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
