OL,3,CForecasters warn of even higher
OL,4,Ctemperatures amid sweltering heatwave
OL,6,FThese alerts are in place until 11pm
OL,7,Fon Friday, and mean "adverse
OL,8,Ftemperatures are likely to impact on
OL,9,Fthe health and wellbeing of the
OL,10,Fpopulation".
OL,12,FThe Met Office has also issued an
OL,13,Famber warning for heat on Friday
OL,14,Fcovering much of England, while a
OL,15,Fyellow warning for thunderstorms is in
OL,16,Fplace for the South West on Thursday
OL,17,Fevening.
OL,26,@oD@UOUrD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782362901
OL,3,CForecasters warn of even higher
OL,4,Ctemperatures amid sweltering heatwave
OL,6,FAnd with the extreme heat set to
OL,7,Flinger in some parts of the country
OL,8,Finto the weekend, the Met Office has
OL,9,Fissued an amber warning for extreme
OL,10,Fheat covering parts of east and south-
OL,11,Feast England on Saturday.
OL,13,FAt least 1,000 schools and nurseries
OL,14,Fwill either be closed or partially
OL,15,Fclosed in England and Wales on
OL,16,FThursday and Friday.
OL,18,FNetwork Rail have advised passengers
OL,19,Fto only travel if "absolutely
OL,20,Fnecessary" on Thursday and Friday.
OL,26,@{D@SOU|D@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
