CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782362901
OL,3,CForecasters warn of even higher
OL,4,Ctemperatures amid sweltering heatwave
OL,6,FIt said that trains will operate at
OL,7,Freduced speeds and on amended
OL,8,Ftimetables, meaning journeys are
OL,9,Flikely to take longer and there is a
OL,10,Fhigher risk of disruption.
OL,12,FThe first record-breaking temperature
OL,13,Frecorded on Wednesday was in
OL,14,FCharlwood, Surrey, which reached 35.7C.
OL,16,FThe figure was surpassed by
OL,17,Fprovisional temperatures of 35.8C at
OL,18,FWiggonholt, West Sussex, 36C in
OL,19,FWisley, Surrey, and then 36.1C in
OL,20,FGosport.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1782362901
OL,3,CForecasters warn of even higher
OL,4,Ctemperatures amid sweltering heatwave
OL,6,FProfessor Stephen Belcher, chief
OL,7,Fscientist for the Met Office, said it
OL,8,Fis "sobering" to see temperatures as
OL,9,Fhigh as this in June.
OL,11,FFigures are currently provisional and
OL,12,Fwould be verified at the end of the
OL,13,Fheatwave to check if it is a new
OL,14,Fnational record.
OL,26,@pD@DOUpD@MO]
